{
  "name": "isleshine",
  "description": "Bright steel pans ringing on a sunny beach, tropical warmth shimmering off the water. Struck steel-drum tones — a deep round low-pan boom holding the island groove floor, a singing tenor-pan lead with shimmering octave and quick metallic glint, a snappier ping-pan answering in sunny counter-melody, a creamy double-second harmony, fast-decaying high pan pings, tiny top-pan flicks scattering like sun on waves, a rolled-pan bloom and a shimmering pan-roll cloud, a near-dry rim-tap pulse, and a beaming little chirp. A major pentatonic, additive and clean, calypso sunshine — carefree, beaming, pure summer joy. Never dark, never harsh.",
  "drone": null,
  "master_gain": 0.45,
  "drone_gain": 0.0,
  "reverb_scale": 1.0,
